    <Data><![CDATA[<h1>Applies to</h1>
  <p>Scala and Play Framework 2.1.0+</p>
  <h1>What to Do</h1>
  <p>Use RSA-2048 whenever strong asymmetric encryption is needed.</p>
  <h1>Why</h1>
  <p>Using strong encryption algorithms helps prevent unauthorized disclosure of sensitive information.</p>
  <h1>How</h1>
  <p>To use strong asymmetric encryption:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        <strong>Use Java cryptographic APIs.</strong>&amp;nbsp;Use the built-in Scala RSA cipher with 2048 bit keys. For an example use RSA.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <strong>Write cryptographic utility functions that use RSA-2048.</strong>&amp;nbsp;Write functions that generate keys, encrypt, and decrypt data.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <strong>Use the utility functions.</strong>&amp;nbsp;Use the cryptographic utility functions whenever data needs to be encrypted or decrypted using symmetric cryptography.</p>
    </li>
  </ol>
